features: No More Messy Shoes: All of family’s shoes piling up in the hallway? Instead of tucking them haphazardly in the corner, you can at least accommodate them in this smart 5-tier shoe rack

Strong Design: 4 open shelves with dense steel mesh offer plenty of space for your shoes; the eye-catching greige surface welcomes bags, keys, picture frames, or a pretty bouquet of roses (top surface holds up to 22 lb, shoe shelves up to 11 lb each)
Assembly Is a No Brainer: Why make things more complicated than they should be? With a simple structure and detailed instructions, you'll have it assembled before you know it
All in Balance: Equipped with adjustable feet, this shoe rack can withstand a spirit level test even on uneven floors; also your tile and wood floors are protected from scratches
What You Get: A 5-tier shoe rack with illustrated instructions, assembly bag and an attractive design from the INDESTIC Collection of VASAGLE to add more charm to your hallway

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful shoe rack!
reviews.reviewText: This lightweight shoe rack was just what I was looking for. Fits many shoes of varying sizes. Easy to put together and overall pretty sturdy though I don’t plan on putting anything too heavy on top. Can hold shoes and some smaller items on the surface.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice shoe rack
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice shoe rack. It holds all of ours shoes with room to spare. It It was easy to put together and it is very sturdy and nice looking. We liked it it so much we bought one for our daughter, so now she can organize all of her shoes. Definitely recommend this shoe rack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and attractive
reviews.reviewText: I've purchased 3 of these and use them for shoes and clothing. They're well built and easy to assemble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble.
reviews.reviewText: It was super easy to assemble. The instructions are easy to read. ALL the parts are clearly labeled. Even the screws/bolts were in labeled bags. It comes with a few spare bolts and those are clearly labeled "spare" on the bag. All I needed was an Allen wrench which was supplied in a bag with the bolts. Probably one of the easiest pieces of furniture I have ever put together. There are adjusters for the feet to make it level and it was so easy. It was way easier to get all the lower shelves' bolts halfway started and wait to tighten them all till everything was assembled.I love this! I put this in my front entry. It is pretty tall, so I do not have to lean over to put anything on top. The lower shelves are sturdy enough to obviously put shoes on, but I would not put anything heavy on them. I was going to only put 2 or 3 lower shelves and put a plant on the lower shelves but the mesh kind of sagged with the weight(20lbs approx), so I decided against it. My plants sit beautifully on the top shelf though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality multipurpose rack
reviews.reviewText: Have purchased 2 of these exact racks now. They are really nice shoe racks. Love the fact we had different color wood options for the top shelf, we have one in our breezeway that honestly is used more as a multipurpose rack ( shoes underneath, dog biscuits, kids book bags, and stuff we need to grab quick on our way out the door on top) it holds a lot of weight without faltering. The lower shelves are made of a wire mesh ( I guess this is good and bad feature .. water/ dirt wont sit on the shelf BUTTT will go through to the next one on another pair of shoes below) also lower shelves have slight indents so not everything just slides right off and the edges on the sides of each rack are slightly raised also just enough to avoid sliding . I do think there may have been some improvements made to the assembly, the last one we purchased about 8 months ago for my son's room and it took 2 of us to put together. This one was easy breezy, took about 45 minutes solo from unboxing. Holes lined up, all the hardware was there and the instructions were simple. If at some point I have the need for another one would buy this exact version again.

reviews.reviewText: Liked the color, materials and height fut my needs for a decent price and overall decent quality. Out of the 4 shelves only one had minor damage. reviews.reviewText: Very attractive with the faux wood top. It was so easy to put together and it easily holds 5 pairs of women's shoes on each level. Perfect for our needs at the front door. However I'll probably need another that has taller shelving with more space on each level to hold boots.
Fits my space perfectly with a classy look.

Easily one of my favourite purchases on Amazon, the building process was relaxing if anything, all the materials for the price are extremely good, and the end product looks fantastic. It’ll comfortably fit 16 shoes and maybe even more if you’ve got smaller feet. Would highly recommend this shelf!
This shoe rack holds 5 pairs of shoes per row, is very sturdy and looks very nice in my entry way. A little pricey but it definitely solves the issue of too many shoes. I am happy with this purchase.
